The given conditions can be interpreted geometrically:

*  $|x + z| = 4$ means $x$ and $-z$ are points on a circle centered at the origin with radius 4.
*  $|y + z| = 4$ means $y$ and $-z$ are points on a circle centered at the origin with radius 4.
*  $|x - y| = 4$ means $x$ and $y$ are points on a circle centered at the origin with radius 4.

Since all three circles have the same radius and pass through the origin, we can visualize this scenario.  Let $-z$ be any point on the circle of radius 4. Then, $x$ and $y$ must lie on the same circle, forming an equilateral triangle with $-z$ as one of the vertices.

