\[[IAD] = \frac{1}{2} \cdot AD \cdot ID = \frac{1}{2} r \cdot AD.\]Then $[ABC] = rs - 2[IAD]$.

Also,
\[[IAD] = [IAB] - [IBD] = \frac{1}{2} cr - \frac{1}{2} br = \frac{1}{2} r(c - b).\]Hence,
\[[ABC] = rs - r(c - b) = r(s - c + b).\]By the Angle Bisector Theorem on triangle $ABD$,
\[\frac{BD}{AD} = \frac{AB}{AD} = \frac{c}{b}.\]Since $BD + AD = c$, $BD = \frac{c^2}{b + c}$ and $AD = \frac{bc}{b + c}$.

By the Angle Bisector Theorem on triangle $ACD$,
\[\frac{CD}{AD} = \frac{AC}{AD} = \frac{b}{c}.\]Since $CD + AD = b$, $CD = \frac{b^2}{b + c}$.

Then
\begin{align*}
[ABC] &= r(s - c + b) \\
&= r \cdot \frac{a + b + c}{2} - r(c - b) \\
&= r \cdot \frac{a - c + 3b}{2} \\
&= r \cdot \frac{a - \frac{b^2}{b + c} + 3b}{2} \\
&= r \cdot \frac{a(b + c) - b^2 + 3b(b + c)}{2(b + c)} \\
&= r \cdot \frac{ab + ac + 2b^2 + 3bc}{2(b + c)}.
\end{align*}We can write
\begin{align*}
ab + ac + 2b^2 + 3bc &= (ab + bc + ca) + (b^2 + 2bc + c^2) - (c^2 - b^2) \\
&= (ab + bc + ca) + (b + c)^2 - (c + b)(c - b) \\
&= (ab + bc + ca) + (b + c)(b + c - c + b) \\
&= (ab + bc + ca) + 2b(b + c).
\end{align*}By the Law of Cosines on triangle $ABC$,
\[a^2 = b^2 + c^2 - 2bc \cos A.\]Then
\[2bc \cos A = b^2 + c^2 - a^2,\]so
\begin{align*}
ab + bc + ca &= ab + bc + \frac{b^2 + c^2 - a^2}{2} \\
&= \frac{2ab + 2bc + b^2 + c^2 - a^2}{2} \\
&= \frac{(b + c)^2 - a^2 + 2ab}{2} \\
&= \frac{(b + c + a)(b + c - a) + 2ab}{2} \\
&= \frac{2s(2s - 2a) + 2ab}{2} \\
&= s(s - a) + ab.
\end{align*}Hence,
\[ab + ac + 2b^2 + 3bc = s(s - a) + ab + 2b(b + c) = s^2 - as + ab + 2b^2 + 2bc.\]Then
\[[ABC] = r \cdot \frac{s^2 - as + ab + 2b^2 + 2bc}{2(b + c)}.\]By Heron's formula,
\[[ABC] = \sqrt{s(s - a)(s - b)(s - c)}.\]Hence,
\[r \cdot \frac{s^2 - as + ab + 2b^2 + 2bc}{2(b + c)} = \sqrt{s(s - a)(s - b)(s - c)}.\]Squaring both sides, we get
\[r^2 \cdot \frac{(s^2 - as + ab + 2b^2 + 2bc)^2}{4(b + c)^2} = s(s - a)(s - b)(s - c).\]Since $r^2 = \frac{(s - a)(s - b)(s - c)}{s}$,
\[\frac{(s - a)(s - b)(s - c)}{s} \cdot \frac{(s^2 - as + ab + 2b^2 + 2bc)^2}{4(b + c)^2} = s(s - a)(s - b)(s - c).\]Then
\[\frac{(s^2 - as + ab + 2b^2 + 2bc)^2}{4s(b + c)^2} = s^2.\]Hence,
\[(s^2 - as + ab + 2b^2 + 2bc)^2 = 4s^3(b + c)^2.\]We can write
\begin{align*}
s^2 - as + ab + 2b^2 + 2bc &= s^2 - as + b(a + 2b + 2c) \\
&= s^2 - as + b(a + b + c + b + c) \\
&= s^2 - as + b(2s + b + c).
\end{align*}Then
\[(s^2 - as + b(2s + b + c))^2 = 4s^3(b + c)^2.\]Expanding, we get
\[s^4 - 2as^3 + a^2 s^2 + 2bs^3 + 2bs^2(b + c) - 2abs^2 - 2ab(b + c)s + b^2 (2s + b + c)^2 = 4s^3(b + c)^2.\]This simplifies to
\[s^4 - 2(a - b) s^3 + (a^2 + 2b^2 + 2bc - 2ab - 4bc) s^2 + (-2ab(b + c) + 4b^2(b + c)) s + b^2 (b + c)^2 = 0.\]This factors as
\[(s - b)^2 (s^2 - 2as + b^2 + 4bc + 4c^2) = 0.\]Since $s > b$, $s^2 - 2as + b^2 + 4bc + 4c^2 = 0$.  By the quadratic formula,
\[s = \frac{2a \pm \sqrt{4a^2 - 4(b^2 + 4bc + 4c^2)}}{2} = a \pm \sqrt{a^2 - (b^2 + 4bc + 4c^2)}.\]Since $s > a$,
\[s = a + \sqrt{a^2 - (b^2 + 4bc + 4c^2)}.\]Then
\[\sqrt{a^2 - (b^2 + 4bc + 4c^2)} = s - a = \frac{b + c - a}{2}.\]Squaring both sides, we get
\[a^2 - (b^2 + 4bc + 4c^2) = \frac{(b + c - a)^2}{4}.\]This simplifies to $a^2 - 2bc = 0$, so $a^2 = 2bc$.

