Therefore, $AH = 2 \cdot AO$, so $A$ is the midpoint of $\overline{HO}$.  Since $X$ lies on line $HO$, triangles $AXH$ and $OAX$ are similar, so
\[\frac{XH}{XA} = \frac{XA}{XO}.\]Then $XH \cdot XO = XA^2 = 49^2$.  Also,
