\[\left( XO + \frac{3}{2} d \right) XO = 49^2.\]Also, $XO + d = XC = XB + BC = 23 + d$, so $XO = 23$.  Hence,
\[\left( 23 + \frac{3}{2} d \right) 23 = 49^2.\]Solving, we find $d = 46$.  Therefore, $XC = 23 + d = \boxed{69}$.

