\[MD = \sqrt{AD^2 - AM^2} = \sqrt{(AP - x)^2 - (300 \sqrt{3})^2}.\]By Pythagoras on right triangle $BMD,$
\[MD = \sqrt{BD^2 - BM^2} = \sqrt{(BP - x)^2 - 300^2}.\]Setting these two expressions for $MD$ equal to each other, we get
\[(AP - x)^2 - (300 \sqrt{3})^2 = (BP - x)^2 - 300^2.\]This simplifies to $AP^2 - 2APx = BP^2 - 2BPx,$ so
\[x = \frac{BP^2 - AP^2}{2(BP - AP)} = \frac{BP + AP}{2} = \frac{BP + 630}{2}.\]By the Law of Sines on $\triangle ABP,$
\[\frac{BP}{\sin \angle BAP} = \frac{AB}{\sin \angle APB}.\]Then
\[BP = \frac{AB \sin \angle BAP}{\sin \angle APB} = \frac{600 \sin \angle OAP}{\sin \angle APB} = \frac{600 \cdot \frac{33}{40 \sqrt{3}}}{\sin \angle APB} = \frac{990 \sqrt{3}}{2 \sin \angle APB}.\]By the Law of Sines on $\triangle AOP,$
\[\frac{AP}{\sin \angle AOP} = \frac{AO}{\sin \angle APB}.\]Then
\[\sin \angle APB = \frac{AO \sin \angle AOP}{AP} = \frac{200 \sqrt{3} \cdot \frac{21}{40 \sqrt{3}}}{630} = \frac{1}{6}.\]Hence, $BP = \frac{990 \sqrt{3}}{2 \cdot \frac{1}{6}} = 2970 \sqrt{3},$ so
\[x = \frac{2970 \sqrt{3} + 630}{2} = \boxed{1785}.\]

