\[P(Y) = \frac{[BIST]}{[BOATIS]} = \frac{1}{3}.\]Also, $P(X | Y) = 1$ (if the dart lands inside $BIST$, then it must land inside exactly one of $BOAT$ and $OTIS$) and $P(X | Y^C) = \frac{1}{2}$ (if the dart lands outside $BIST$, then it has an equal chance of landing inside $BOAT$ as it does of landing inside $OTIS$).

Therefore,
\begin{align*}
P(X) &= P(X | Y) P(Y) + P(X | Y^C) P(Y^C) \\
