\[\overrightarrow{H} = \overrightarrow{B} + 2 \overrightarrow{BD} = \overrightarrow{B} + 2 \left( \frac{1}{2} (\overrightarrow{B} + \overrightarrow{C}) - \overrightarrow{B} \right) = \overrightarrow{C} - \overrightarrow{B} = 12 \text{cis } c - 12 \text{cis } b.\]Hence,
\begin{align*}
OH^2 &= |\overrightarrow{H}|^2 \\
&= |12 \text{cis } c - 12 \text{cis } b|^2 \\
&= |12 (\cos c + i \sin c) - 12 (\cos b + i \sin b)|^2 \\
&= 12^2 |(\cos c - \cos b) + i (\sin c - \sin b)|^2 \\
&= 12^2 ((\cos c - \cos b)^2 + (\sin c - \sin b)^2) \\
&= 12^2 (\cos^2 c - 2 \cos c \cos b + \cos^2 b + \sin^2 c - 2 \sin c \sin b + \sin^2 b) \\
