Imagine coloring the grid like a checkerboard, alternating black and white cells.  Notice that cards in cells of the same color are never adjacent. This means we can choose the arrangement of ranks for the black squares independently of the arrangement of ranks for the white squares, and similarly for the suits.

[asy]
