\[\sqrt{3} n = 2a \sqrt{n - b^2} + 2b \sqrt{n - a^2}.\]Squaring both sides, we get
\[3n^2 = 4a^2 (n - b^2) + 4b^2 (n - a^2) + 8ab \sqrt{(n - a^2)(n - b^2)}.\]This simplifies to $n^2 = 8ab \sqrt{(n - a^2)(n - b^2)},$ so
\[n^4 = 64a^2 b^2 (n - a^2)(n - b^2).\]Let $x = a^2$ and $y = b^2.$  Then
