[/asy]

There are $6$ choices for the color that is used twice.  Once this color is chosen, the other two colors are determined.  There are $2$ ways to arrange the colors around the square (clockwise or counterclockwise).

**Step 2: Extend to the whole grid**

Now, consider a row of squares.  Once we color the edges of one square, the colors of the edges of the square to its right are forced. 

[asy]
unitsize(1cm);
for (int i=0; i<=7; ++i) {
draw((i,0)--(i+1,0)--(i+1,1)--(i,1)--cycle);
}
