\[-\sqrt{x^2 - 100} + x - y < -\sqrt{x^2 - 100} + 20.\]We can make $-\sqrt{x^2 - 100} + 20$ arbitrarily close to 20 by taking $x$ arbitrarily close to 10.  Therefore, the area of $\gamma_3$ can be made arbitrarily close to $20^2 \pi = 400 \pi$, but it cannot be equal to $400 \pi$.  The greatest integer less than $400 \pi$ is $\boxed{1256}$.

