We count the number of such graphs.  Suppose there are $k$ cycles.  Then $k$ of the vertices are fixed points of the cycles.  The remaining $7-k$ vertices can each choose any of the $k$ cycles to be part of, for $k^{7-k}$ choices.

Thus, the answer is
\[\sum_{k=1}^7 k^{7-k} \cdot \frac{7!}{k!(7-k)!} = 7 + 210 + 1764 + 4620 + 3780 + 720 + 24 = \boxed{107}.\]

