Since $\triangle DEF$ is isosceles right, we have $DE = DF$.  By the Pythagorean Theorem on triangles $CDE$ and $ADF$,
\begin{align*}
DE^2 &= x^2 + (12 - x)^2, \\
DF^2 &= y^2 + (5 - y)^2.
