\[x^2 + (12 - x)^2 = y^2 + (5 - y)^2.\]This simplifies to $24x - 144 = -10y + 25$, or $24x + 10y = 169$.

Also, by the Pythagorean Theorem on triangle $ABC$,
\[EF^2 = DE^2 + DF^2 = 2x^2 - 24x + 144 + 2y^2 - 10y + 25 = 2x^2 + 2y^2 - 24x - 10y + 169.\]Since $EF = BF \sqrt{2} = 3 \sqrt{2}$, $EF^2 = 18$, so
\[2x^2 + 2y^2 - 24x - 10y + 169 = 18.\]This simplifies to $x^2 + y^2 - 12x - 5y + 75 = 0$.

We can rewrite the equation $24x + 10y = 169$ as $y = \frac{169 - 24x}{10}$.  Substituting into $x^2 + y^2 - 12x - 5y + 75 = 0$, we get
